Catalan's constant.item_description: the Dirichlet beta function at two

Graham's number.item_description: enormously large number, the upper bound solution to a Ramsey theory problem

phase velocity.item_description: rate at which the phase of the wave propagates in space

velocity.item_description: rate of change of the position of an object as a function of time, and the direction of that change

power.item_description: rate at which energy is transferred, used, or transformed

pressure.item_description: ratio of force applied over an area

force.item_description: influence that causes an object to change motion

radius.item_description: segment in a circle or sphere (from its center to its perimeter or surface) and its length

bulk density.item_description: density of a material in a fixed volume

relative atomic mass.item_description: dimensionless physical quantity: ratio of the average mass of atoms of an element (in a given sample) to one unified atomic mass unit.The unified atomic mass unit, symbol u, is defined being  1⁄12 of the mass of a carbon-12 atom

distance.item_description: straight line that connects two points in a measurable space or in an observable physical space

standard atomic weight.item_description: relative atomic mass as defined by IUPAC (CIAAW)

reaction rate.item_description: for a reactant or product in a particular reaction is intuitively defined as how quickly or slowly a reaction takes place

conventional atomic weight.item_description: from standard atiomic weight range, reduced to a single value

Exhaust gas mass flow.item_description: flow of exhaust gases per unit time

mass.item_description: measure of the resistance of a physical body to acceleration; also determines the strength of its gravitational attraction

Q496818.item_description: third coordinate in a measured space with dimension 3 or higher

red shift.item_description: increase in wavelength (decrease in frequency) of an electromagnetic radiation

height.item_description: distance between the lowest end and highest end of an object

hydraulic head.item_description: specific measurement of liquid pressure above a geodetic datum

speed of light.item_description: speed at which all massless particles and associated fields travel in vacuum

Avogadro constant.item_description: fundamental physical constant (symbols: L,Nᴀ) representing the molar number of entities

area.item_description: quantity that expresses the extent of a two-dimensional surface or shape, or planar lamina, in the plane

Damk\u00f6hler numbers.item_description: dimensionless numbers used in chemical engineering

activity.item_description: measure of the effective concentration of a species in a mixture

Karlovitz number.item_description: dimensionless number used in chemical engineering

acceleration.item_description: rate at which the velocity of a body changes with time, and the direction in which that change is acting

special orthogonal group.item_description: connected component of O(n) containing the identity

duration.item_description: length of time of an event or process; quality of an event or process with beginning and end

median lethal concentration.item_description: statistically derived median concentration of a substance in an environmental medium expected to kill 50% of organisms in a given population under a defined set of conditions

time.item_description: dimension in which events can be ordered from the past through the present into the future

reaction rate constant.item_description: quantifies the rate of a chemical reaction

permeability.item_description: measure of the ability of a porous material to allow fluids to pass through it

Boltzmann constant.item_description: physical constant relating energy at the individual particle level with temperature

temperature.item_description: physical property of matter that quantitatively expresses the common notions of hot and cold

hydraulic conductivity.item_description: measure of the ability of a porous material to allow water to pass through it

specific storage.item_description: the amount of water that a portion of an aquifer releases from storage, per unit mass or volume of aquifer, per unit change in hydraulic head

volumetric flow rate.item_description: volume of fluid which passes per unit time

length.item_description: measured dimension of an object in a physical space

voltage.item_description: difference in the electric potential between two points in space

ordinate.item_description: second coordinate in a measured space with dimension 2 or higher

electric charge.item_description: physical property that quantifies an object's interaction with electric fields

torque.item_description: tendency of a force to rotate an object

electrical resistance.item_description: opposition to the passage of an electric current

median lethal dose.item_description: the dose required to kill half the members of a tested population after a specified test duration (LC₅₀ → P2712)

diameter.item_description: straight line segment that passes through the center of a circle

orbital eccentricity.item_description: parameter that determines the amount by which an orbit deviates from a perfect circle

elementary charge.item_description: the electric charge carried by a single proton or a single electron

porosity.item_description: measure of the void spaces in a material

principal quantum number.item_description: one of four quantum numbers which are assigned to each electron in an atom to describe that electron's state

relative density.item_description: ratio of the density (mass of a unit volume) of a substance to the density of a given reference material

thickness.item_description: extent from one surface to the opposite, usually in the smallest solid dimension

atomic number.item_description: number of protons found in the nucleus of an atom

minimal lethal concentration.item_description: Lowest concentration of a toxic substance in an environmental medium that kills individual organisms or test species under a defined set of conditions

magnetic induction.item_description: production of a potential difference across a conductor when it is exposed to a varying magnetic field

energy.item_description: quantitative physical property transferred to objects to perform heating or work on them

abscissa.item_description: first coordinate in a measured space with dimension 1 or higher

electric current density.item_description: electric current per unit area of cross section

rotation.item_description: circular movement of an object around a center (or point) of rotation . A three-dimensional object always rotates around an imaginary line called a rotation axis

frequency.item_description: number of occurrences per unit time
